Flags on Track: What does the red and yellow striped flag indicate?

answer_options.answer_text: Danger, the driver must slow down, something has beyond the flag station, no overtaking unless directed by the track marshals.

text: Front Impact Attenuator Systems: What is true regarding the Anti Intrusion Plate (AIP), the Impact Attenuator (IA) and its surroundings?

answer_options.answer_text: A rectangular 350x380mm AIP may be attached to the front bulkhead using 15 M6 grade 8.8 bolts
If a standard aluminium honeycomb IA is bonded to a 4mm think aluminium AIP, there is no circumstance where officials can require additional physical testing or changes to the design
A rectangular 350x380 AIP may be attached to the front bulkhead using 4 M10 grade 12.9 bolts if equivalent strangth to the required number of M8 grade 8.8 bolts can be shown
No part of any IA may be above 350mm from the ground during the tech inspection
